cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with clustering multi-view data, which is a fundamental research topic in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The proposed method involves deep generative learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also deals with learning a shared generative latent representation, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves capturing correlations among all the views, which is a common technique in natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely category. Finally, the paper involves dealing with large-scale datasets, which is a common challenge in multimedia computing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category.
